# **Part 2**

## **Describe a time when you worked in a group.**

One experience that immediately comes to mind was a group project I worked on during university. It was for one of our computer science courses, and our task was to design a simple intelligent transportation management system. Since the project was too large and complicated for one person to finish alone, we were divided into a group of four students.

In the group, my main responsibility was programming and system design. More specifically, I worked on the backend logic and helped integrate different parts of the project together. The other members focused on areas like user interface design, data collection, and presentation preparation. At the beginning, everything seemed to go quite smoothly because everyone was enthusiastic and motivated.

However, we also faced several problems during the process. One major issue was communication. Since everyone had different schedules and working styles, it was sometimes difficult to coordinate meetings or make decisions efficiently. Another challenge was that some technical problems turned out to be harder than we expected. For example, at one point, different parts of the system couldn’t connect properly because of compatibility issues in the code. We spent quite a long time debugging and discussing possible solutions.

Even though the process was stressful at times, I think working in a group was still very valuable. One reason is that we were able to combine different skills and ideas, which made the final project much better than what one person could probably achieve alone. More importantly, I learned a lot about teamwork, communication, and responsibility. In real life, especially in fields like technology and engineering, people rarely work completely independently, so I think experiences like this are extremely useful for future careers.

---

## **中文翻译：**

我立刻想到的是大学期间的一次小组项目。那是我们计算机专业的一门课程，我们的任务是设计一个简单的智能交通管理系统。因为这个项目对一个人来说太复杂了，所以我们被分成了四人小组。

在团队里，我主要负责编程和系统设计，更具体地说，是后端逻辑以及整合不同模块。其他成员则负责界面设计、数据收集和汇报展示。刚开始的时候一切都挺顺利，因为大家都很有热情。

不过过程中我们也遇到了不少问题。最大的一个问题是沟通。由于每个人时间安排和做事方式不同，所以有时很难高效地协调会议或者做决定。另一个挑战是，一些技术问题比我们预想中更复杂。比如有一次系统不同模块之间无法正常连接，因为代码兼容性出现了问题。我们花了很长时间调试和讨论解决方案。

虽然过程有时挺有压力，但我还是觉得团队合作非常有价值。因为大家可以结合不同的技能和想法，让最终成果比一个人单独完成更好。更重要的是，我学到了很多关于团队合作、沟通和责任感的东西。在现实生活中，尤其是科技和工程领域，人们很少完全独立工作，所以这样的经历对未来非常有帮助。

